ZCZC OE83
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 182300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO BE CENTRED CLOSE TO S CORNWALL
AROUND 1027 WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING NE INTO SCANDINAVIA. AT THE SAME TIME
LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO THE SW OF ICELAND AROUND 995. THROUGH WEDNESDAY AND
THURSDAY THE LOW PRESSURE DRIFTS NE ACROSS ICELAND WITH A NEW DPN LOW LIKELY
TO MOV QCKY NE CLOSE TO FAEROES. AN ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGH MOV ERRATICALLY
S ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES THROUGH THURSDAY AND FRIDAY WITH THE CHANCE OF
A DEVELOPING WAVE PERHAPS WITH A SHALLOW LOW. HOWEVER THIS IS LOW CONFIDENCE.
MEANWHILE THE HIGH DRIFTS E INTO EERN EUROPE WITH A NEW HIGH FORMING MID
N ATLANTIC 1032 BY FRIDAY. THE MAIN RISK OF NEAR GALE TO GALE FORCE WINDS
DEVELOPING IS LATER WEDNESDAY INTO EARLY THURSDAY INITIALLY ACROSS N SHANNON
AND ROCKALL THEN ACROSS NERN-MOST AND NWERN-MOST PORTPATRICK. STRG WINDS
LIKELY IN THE FAR N OF PORTPATRICK THROUGH THE REMAINDER OF THURSDAY AND
